{
  "name": "5 \u00b7 Wiki Maintenance (weekly, manual)",
  "version": "2.0.1",
  "description": "Weekly (Friday) wiki maintenance. FULLY AUTONOMOUS. Runs 10 stages: 5 pipeline stages (enrich state files, publish, edit, write, generate ideas) that invoke wiki-team agents via kiro-cli, plus 5 audit/housekeeping stages (consume candidates, refresh SP cache, rebuild index, lint audit, roadmap update). Each pipeline stage has a pre-check and skips silently when nothing is eligible; state-file enrichment + idea generation always run. Replaces the propose-only v1.x hook which produced review-queue pileup but zero pipeline throughput.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run weekly wiki maintenance. FULLY AUTONOMOUS \u2014 do NOT ask Richard for input at any stage. Make all decisions yourself; flag blockers in the final report but don't pause for them. PT date: run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date +%Y-%m-%d`.\n\n**kiro-cli invocation pattern (CORRECTED from v1.x):** Positional argument, NOT stdin. Use `PROMPT=$(cat /tmp/prompt.txt) && kiro-cli chat --agent <agent> --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never \"$PROMPT\"` OR inline `kiro-cli chat --agent <agent> --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never \"$(cat /tmp/prompt.txt)\"`. Piping prompts via `echo | kiro-cli` FAILS with 'Input must be supplied when running in non-interactive mode' \u2014 kiro-cli reads the first positional arg as the question, ignores piped stdin in chat mode.\n\nTwo halves:\n  **Half A \u2014 Pipeline (stages 1-5)** invoke wiki-team agents via kiro-cli. Actual content work happens here.\n  **Half B \u2014 Housekeeping (stages 6-10)** orchestrator-only. Audit, cache, index, roadmap, report.\n\nRun Half A first so Half B sees the results. Total wall-clock ~20-30 min.\n\n---\n\n## HALF A \u2014 Pipeline\n\n### Stage 1: Enrich state files (ALWAYS RUNS, no skip)\n\nThe 3 state files in `~/shared/wiki/state-files/` are Richard's most-referenced artifacts. They get a dated \"Recent signal\" section every run.\n\nFor each of the 3 state files (au-paid-search-state.md, mx-paid-search-state.md, ww-testing-state.md):\n\n1. Query DuckDB for the past 7 days of signal scoped to the market:\n   - `SELECT topic, source_channel, source_author, ts, snippet FROM signals.signal_tracker WHERE (LOWER(topic) LIKE '%{market}%' OR LOWER(snippet) LIKE '%{market}%') AND ts > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP - INTERVAL '7 days' ORDER BY ts DESC LIMIT 20`\n   - `SELECT event_date, event_type, description FROM main.project_timeline WHERE project_key LIKE '%{market}%' AND event_date > CURRENT_DATE - 7 ORDER BY event_date DESC`\n   - For ww-testing-state: query `signals.signal_tracker` scoped to testing topics (WHERE topic IN ('polaris-brand-lp', 'oci-rollout', 'ai-max', 'email-overlay', 'email-overlay-ww-rollout', 'ieccp-planning')) instead of market-scoped.\n\n2. Build a brief fact-sheet (bullet list, 500-1000 chars) from those rows and invoke wiki-writer:\n   `echo \"<prompt>\" | kiro-cli chat --agent wiki-writer --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never`\n   Prompt: \"Enrich `{state_file_path}` with a new dated subsection under the 'Recent signal' heading (create the heading if missing). Today is {YYYY-MM-DD}. Here are the new signals from the past 7 days:\\n\\n{fact_sheet}\\n\\nWrite a 3-5 bullet subsection titled `### {YYYY-MM-DD} \u2014 weekly enrichment` that summarizes the substantive items. Skip trivial signals. If nothing is substantive, write a single line: `No substantive new signal this week.` Update the file's `updated:` frontmatter field to today's date. Do not modify other sections.\"\n\n3. If writer returns \"No substantive new signal this week\", still bump the `updated:` frontmatter so the dashboard shows freshness. Report per-file status in the final summary.\n\n### Stage 2: Publish (skip silently if no eligible article)\n\nFind any article where BOTH Eval A and Eval B critic reviews exist in `~/shared/wiki/reviews/` with APPROVE verdicts AND the article still has `status: REVIEW`:\n\n1. Grep `~/shared/wiki/reviews/*-eval-a.md` for `Verdict: PUBLISH|APPROVE`, then check for matching `*-eval-b.md` with `Verdict: SHIPS|APPROVE`.\n2. For each match, confirm the corresponding article at `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/**/<slug>.md` has `status: REVIEW`.\n3. If \u22651 eligible: invoke wiki-librarian for the first one:\n   `echo \"<prompt>\" | kiro-cli chat --agent wiki-librarian --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never`\n   Prompt: \"Publish `{article_path}`. The two reviews at `~/shared/wiki/reviews/{slug}-eval-a.md` and `{slug}-eval-b.md` both APPROVED. Run the three publish gates per wiki-pipeline-rules.md \u00a78: (1) confirm both critic verdicts APPROVE, (2) confirm `## Constraint check` section present in both reviews with all PASS, (3) confirm zero `<!-- TODO: cite -->` or `<!-- TODO: constraint conflict -->` markers in the article. If all three pass, flip frontmatter `status:` from REVIEW to FINAL, bump `updated:` to today, append to `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/wiki-index.md` if not already present, and report. If any gate fails, do NOT flip status; write the specific gate failure to `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/revision-queue.md` and report back to reversion.\"\n4. Note: sharepoint-sync hook (userTriggered) picks up FINAL articles on its next run \u2014 do NOT push to SharePoint here.\n5. If 0 eligible: report \"Publish: nothing eligible (no DRAFT article has cleared both critic reviews)\" and proceed.\n\n### Stage 3: Edit (skip silently if no DRAFT)\n\nFind the oldest article with `status: DRAFT` in `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/**`:\n\n1. Grep frontmatter for `status: DRAFT`, sort by `updated:` ascending, pick the first.\n2. If none: report \"Edit: nothing to review (no DRAFT articles)\" and proceed.\n3. Invoke wiki-critic TWICE as separate kiro-cli calls per pipeline-rules \u00a71 (Eval A and Eval B must not see each other's output):\n   - Eval A (strict rubric): `echo \"<prompt>\" | kiro-cli chat --agent wiki-critic --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never` with prompt \"Mode: Eval A (strict rubric). Review `{article_path}` per the 5-dimension rubric in your agent definition: Usefulness, Clarity, Accuracy, Dual-audience, Economy. Start with the `## Constraint check` section enumerating each constraint from the article's frontmatter `constraints:` list as PASS or VIOLATED. Any VIOLATED = verdict REVISE. Also grep for `<!-- TODO: cite -->` markers \u2014 any present = REVISE. Then score each dimension 0-10 with one-sentence justification. Overall \u22658 with no dim <7 = verdict PUBLISH. Write review to `~/shared/wiki/reviews/{slug}-eval-a.md`.\"\n   - Eval B (reader simulation): same pattern but with prompt \"Mode: Eval B (reader simulation). Simulate the target reader for `{article_path}` (per the article's `audience:` frontmatter \u2014 Leadership=Kate, Team=Brandon, Personal=Richard). Would they ship this with their name on it? Same 5-dimension rubric, same \u22658/no-dim-<7 bar. Start with the `## Constraint check` section. Write review to `~/shared/wiki/reviews/{slug}-eval-b.md`.\"\n4. Report verdict pair. If both APPROVE, this article will be picked up by Stage 2 next run. If either REVISE, note which dimension failed.\n\n### Stage 4: Write (skip silently if no eligible P1 in review-queue)\n\nRead `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/review-queue.md`. Find the first unchecked P1 proposal (pattern `- [ ] **P1 \u2014` or `- [ ] **{slug}`):\n\n1. If no unchecked P1: report \"Write: no P1 proposals pending\" and proceed.\n2. Extract the slug and the signal summary from the proposal entry.\n3. Invoke wiki-researcher first:\n   `echo \"<prompt>\" | kiro-cli chat --agent wiki-researcher --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never`\n   Prompt: \"Research brief for new wiki article `{slug}`. Signal context: `{signal_summary}`. Draft a research brief at `~/shared/wiki/research/{slug}-brief.md` with: purpose, audience, scope, key claims to investigate, sources to cross-reference (slack/hedy/asana/internal wiki), and a mandatory `## Constraints` section per wiki-pipeline-rules.md \u00a78 listing hard priors as one-sentence declarative statements (if no topic-specific constraints, write 'No additional constraints beyond the style guide and audience-by-doc-type defaults.'). 600-1200 words.\"\n4. Then invoke wiki-writer against the brief:\n   `echo \"<prompt>\" | kiro-cli chat --agent wiki-writer --no-interactive --trust-all-tools --wrap never`\n   Prompt: \"Draft wiki article `{slug}` based on `~/shared/wiki/research/{slug}-brief.md`. Write to `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/<category>/{slug}.md` with `status: DRAFT` frontmatter. Copy the brief's `## Constraints` list into frontmatter as YAML `constraints:` list. Cite every substantive claim inline \u2014 use `<!-- TODO: cite -->` markers for any assertion you can't source. Follow wiki-pipeline-rules.md all sections. Pick `doc-type:` per \u00a79 heuristic. Assume `audience: amazon-internal` unless brief says otherwise.\"\n5. Flip the checkbox in review-queue.md from `- [ ]` to `- [x]` and append ` \u2014 drafted YYYY-MM-DD, awaiting wiki-critic (next run's Stage 3).`\n\n### Stage 5: Generate ideas (ALWAYS RUNS, no skip)\n\nAlways produce 3-5 new-article candidates even if other sources are empty. Fallback sources in order:\n\n1. **Primary: `signals.wiki_candidates` view.** Query top topics by quality_score that don't match any existing wiki article slug. `SELECT topic, quality_score, total_mentions, channel_spread FROM signals.wiki_candidates ORDER BY quality_score DESC LIMIT 10`. Cross-reference against `wiki-index.md` to filter out existing articles.\n2. **Secondary: freshly-archived wiki-candidates.md lines from this run's Phase 1.** Cluster by proposed slug, pick any slug with \u22653 independent session mentions.\n3. **Tertiary: audit findings.** If audit (Stage 9 below, which has already run \u2014 coordinate ordering) finds a concentration of low-quality articles (short, no frontmatter, orphaned), propose a \"strategic rewrite\" candidate.\n4. **Tertiary: upgrade candidates.** Scan wiki-index for articles where `word_count < 500` and `status: REVIEW` (thin articles sitting in REVIEW). Propose each as an \"expand and re-review\" candidate with a specific shape for what's missing.\n5. **Quaternary:** always ask \"what are Richard's next 2 calendar-visible artifacts (Testing Approach revs, MBR, skip-level) and is a supporting wiki doc justified?\" Scan the calendar_week view for upcoming leadership-visible sessions.\n\nOutput: append a dated subsection to `review-queue.md` with 3-5 proposals at P1-P3. Each proposal must include: signal evidence (channels + mention counts OR article paths for upgrades), proposed audience + doc-type, acceptance criteria (one sentence on what the article ships for).\n\n---\n\n## HALF B \u2014 Housekeeping\n\n### Stage 6: Consume wiki-candidates.md\n\nRead `~/shared/context/intake/wiki-candidates.md`. For every candidate line since the last archive marker:\n1. Dedupe by slug similarity.\n2. Group signals across hooks.\n3. Cross-ref against `wiki-index.md`.\n4. Promote the top 3-5 to `review-queue.md` (if not already there from Stage 5).\n5. Archive processed lines to `~/shared/context/intake/archive/wiki-candidates-YYYY-WNN.md`.\n\n### Stage 7: Refresh SharePoint cache + rebuild index\n\nSharePoint layout v2 (adopted 2026-04-28): crawl targets are:\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Team/programs/{oci, polaris, ai-max, aeo-ai-overviews, ieccp-planning, agentic-ps, op1-testing-framework}\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Team/methodology/{kiro-for-team, testing, handoffs, callouts, reporting}\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Team/library/{daily-briefs, ad-copy-results, competitor-intel, meeting-briefs, research-clips}\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Team/markets/{au, mx, us, ca, jp, uk, de, fr, it, es, eu5, ww}\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Dashboards (top-level)\n  - AB-Paid-Acq-Ops/{audit-logs, agent-state, tools, portable-body}\n  - .Richard-Private/** \u2014 INTENTIONALLY EXCLUDED\n\n1. Call `sharepoint_list_files(libraryName=\"Documents\", folderPath=\"<path>\", personal=true, top=200)` for each folder. Build `{<folder>: [<file_records>]}` JSON.\n2. Pipe that JSON to `python3 ~/shared/dashboards/refresh-sharepoint-cache.py` on stdin. The script writes `data/sharepoint-artifacts.json` with layout_version:2, skips _index.md/README.md, de-dupes by newest mtime.\n3. Run `python3 ~/shared/dashboards/build-wiki-index.py` then `python3 ~/shared/dashboards/build-wiki-health-history.py`.\n4. Expected output: `SharePoint: N published / M local-only / K published-stale` + `Wiki index .md: ...`.\n5. If Stage 2 published an article this run, the published count should be +1 vs last week. Log the delta.\n\n### Stage 8: Wiki lint audit\n\n1. Orphan scan: `find shared/wiki/agent-created -name '*.md'` vs `wiki-index.md` Total.\n2. Stale by 4-bucket vocab (wiki-pipeline-rules.md \u00a79): tactical >90d, reference >540d, strategy+review_due overdue; skip snapshot and foundational:true; unset doc-type flagged as retag-pending with legacy >90d rule.\n3. Broken relative .md refs.\n4. Missing required frontmatter (title/status/audience/owner).\n5. SharePoint-stale count from wiki-search-index.json.\n6. Local REVIEW+unpublished count (informational; not action unless pipeline has run this cycle).\n7. Signal-based freshness: `signals.wiki_candidates` top-N.\n\nWrite to `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/health-YYYY-MM-DD.md` + `audit-YYYY-MM-DD.md`.\n\n### Stage 9: Roadmap update\n\nUpdate `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/roadmap.md`:\n- Mark completed items from Stage 2 Publish as Done.\n- Mark in-progress items from Stage 4 Write as Active.\n- Add new proposals from Stages 5/6 to Queued.\n- Prune items Done >30 days to Archived.\n\n### Stage 10: Report\n\nFinal summary (compact):\n- Pipeline: enriched N state files, published N, edited N (verdict pair), wrote N, generated N ideas.\n- Housekeeping: consumed N candidates, SharePoint delta +/-N published, audit results (healthy/stale/orphan/broken), ideas count.\n- Any agent invocations that failed or returned unexpected output \u2014 flag without blocking.\n- Any Richard-visible blockers that should go to session-log OPEN items.\n\n---\n\n## KILL CONDITIONS\n\n- 2026-06-01: if the wiki-candidates contribution queue has produced <3 articles Richard promoted (across any stage) AND state-file enrichments weren't useful (Richard says so or they go unreferenced), revert hook contributions and delete wiki-candidates.md.\n- 2026-07-01: if Stage 2 Publish has fired <4 times total (i.e., articles aren't making it through critic gates), the constraint-replacement protocol (\u00a78) isn't working \u2014 revisit whether structural state (blackboard or equivalent) needs to come back.\n- If any single run takes >45 minutes wall-clock, stop and investigate which stage stalled."
  }
}
